	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It was used by Famicom pirates in the 80s to sell games that otherwise wouldn't work on their hardware.
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It's not really about "emulating a mapper", it's about hacking the bankswitching code to call WRAM code instead.</div>Well that WRAM code processes the input into discrete writes for the copier hardware and will dump kilobytes of PRG ROM out $2007 to run CHR bankswitched games on CHR-RAM.
<br />
<br />Most games with WRAM can still have trainers, of course it's more work to move things, but it happens.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


